Usage: create_library_set [-help] [-aocv <string>]
                          [-library_side_file <string>] [-link_timing <string>]
                          -name <libSetName> [-si <string>] [-socv <string>]
                          [-target_timing <string>] [-timing <string>]

-help                             # Prints out the command usage
-aocv <string>                    # Specifies the aocv libraries to include in
                                  # the library set (string, optional)
-library_side_file <string>       # Specifies library side file
                                  # (string, optional)
-link_timing <string>             # Specifies the link timing libraries to
                                  # include in the library set (string, optional)
-name <libSetName>                # Specifies the name for the library set
                                  # being created (string, required)
-si <string>                      # Specifies cdB libraries and/or user-defined
                                  # noise (UDN) models to include in the
                                  # library set (string, optional)
-socv <string>                    # Specifies the socv libraries to include in
                                  # the library set (string, optional)
-target_timing <string>           # Specifies the target timing libraries to
                                  # include in the library set (string, optional)
-timing <string>                  # Specifies the timing libraries to include
                                  # in the library set (string, optional)